parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the fuel tank can cause fuel to leak, creating a fire or explosion hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Gas fumes are present while driving or parked
puddles of fuel are visible underneath the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel pump/filter assembly can cause fuel to leak, creating a fire or explosion hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Gas fumes are present while driving or parked
puddles of fuel are visible underneath the vehicle
hairline cracks in the fuel pump/filter assembly "cap" on top of the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inconsistent RPM readings can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

The failure of the green 16-gauge copper wire in the ignition switch wire loom can cause the engine to die, lights to go out, and all power to the motorcycle to be lost, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: and all power to the motorcycle is lost
often while the bike is in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the front fork can cause the motorcycle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The front fork breaks or collapses
causing the motorcycle to wobble or become unstable
leading to loss of control and potential crashes.
